## ðŸŽ¤ Interview-Ready Points

### â“ When asked *"Why use load balancers?"*
- âœ… Prevents single point of failure
- âœ… Improves performance through distribution  
- âœ… Enables horizontal scaling
- âœ… Provides redundancy

### â“ When asked *"Where would you place them?"*
- ðŸŒ User-facing layer (web servers)
- âš™ï¸ Internal services layer (microservices)
- ðŸ—„ï¸ Data layer (database replicas)

---

## ðŸ’¡ Key Takeaway

Load balancing is like having **multiple cashiers at a supermarket** instead of one. It prevents long queues, handles peak traffic better, and if one cashier goes on break, others keep serving customers. 

> **Essential for any system expecting real traffic!**

